5154/**
5155 * ext4_trim_all_free -- function to trim all free space in alloc. group
5156 * @sb: super block for file system
5157 * @group: group to be trimmed
5158 * @start: first group block to examine
5159 * @max: last group block to examine
5160 * @minblocks: minimum extent block count
5161 *
5162 * ext4_trim_all_free walks through group's buddy bitmap searching for free
5163 * extents. When the free block is found, ext4_trim_extent is called to TRIM
5164 * the extent.
5165 *
5166 *
5167 * ext4_trim_all_free walks through group's block bitmap searching for free
5168 * extents. When the free extent is found, mark it as used in group buddy
5169 * bitmap. Then issue a TRIM command on this extent and free the extent in
5170 * the group buddy bitmap. This is done until whole group is scanned.
5171 */
5172static ext4_grpblk_t
5173ext4_trim_all_free(struct super_block *sb, ext4_group_t group,
5174 ext4_grpblk_t start, ext4_grpblk_t max,
5175 ext4_grpblk_t minblocks)
5176{
5177 void *bitmap;
5178 ext4_grpblk_t next, count = 0, free_count = 0;
5179 struct ext4_buddy e4b;
5180 int ret = 0;
5181
5182 trace_ext4_trim_all_free(sb, group, start, max);
5183
5184 ret = ext4_mb_load_buddy(sb, group, &e4b);
5185 if (ret) {
5186 ext4_warning(sb, "Error %d loading buddy information for %u",
5187 ret, group);
5188 return ret;
5189 }
5190 bitmap = e4b.bd_bitmap;
5191
5192 ext4_lock_group(sb, group);
5193 if (EXT4_MB_GRP_WAS_TRIMMED(e4b.bd_info) &&
5194 minblocks >= atomic_read(&EXT4_SB(sb)->s_last_trim_minblks))
5195 goto out;
5196
5197 start = (e4b.bd_info->bb_first_free > start) ?
5198 e4b.bd_info->bb_first_free : start;
5199
5200 while (start <= max) {
5201 start = mb_find_next_zero_bit(bitmap, max + 1, start);
5202 if (start > max)
5203 break;
5204 next = mb_find_next_bit(bitmap, max + 1, start);
5205
5206 if ((next - start) >= minblocks) {
5207 ret = ext4_trim_extent(sb, start,
5208 next - start, group, &e4b);
5209 if (ret && ret != -EOPNOTSUPP)
5210 break;
5211 ret = 0;
5212 count += next - start;
5213 }
5214 free_count += next - start;
5215 start = next + 1;
5216
5217 if (fatal_signal_pending(current)) {
5218 count = -ERESTARTSYS;
5219 break;
5220 }
5221
5222 if (need_resched()) {
5223 ext4_unlock_group(sb, group);
5224 cond_resched();
5225 ext4_lock_group(sb, group);
5226 }
5227
5228 if ((e4b.bd_info->bb_free - free_count) < minblocks)
5229 break;
5230 }
5231
5232 if (!ret) {
5233 ret = count;
5234 EXT4_MB_GRP_SET_TRIMMED(e4b.bd_info);
5235 }
5236out:
5237 ext4_unlock_group(sb, group);
5238 ext4_mb_unload_buddy(&e4b);
5239
5240 ext4_debug("trimmed %d blocks in the group %d\n",
5241 count, group);
5242
5243 return ret;
5244}

5246/**
5247 * ext4_trim_fs() -- trim ioctl handle function
5248 * @sb: superblock for filesystem
5249 * @range: fstrim_range structure
5250 *
5251 * start: First Byte to trim
5252 * len: number of Bytes to trim from start
5253 * minlen: minimum extent length in Bytes
5254 * ext4_trim_fs goes through all allocation groups containing Bytes from
5255 * start to start+len. For each such a group ext4_trim_all_free function
5256 * is invoked to trim all free space.
5257 */
5258int ext4_trim_fs(struct super_block *sb, struct fstrim_range *range)
5259{
5260 struct ext4_group_info *grp;
5261 ext4_group_t group, first_group, last_group;
5262 ext4_grpblk_t cnt = 0, first_cluster, last_cluster;
5263 uint64_t start, end, minlen, trimmed = 0;
5264 ext4_fsblk_t first_data_blk =
5265 le32_to_cpu(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_es->s_first_data_block);
5266 ext4_fsblk_t max_blks = ext4_blocks_count(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_es);
5267 int ret = 0;
5268
5269 start = range->start >> sb->s_blocksize_bits;
5270 end = start + (range->len >> sb->s_blocksize_bits) - 1;
5271 minlen = EXT4_NUM_B2C(EXT4_SB(sb),
5272 range->minlen >> sb->s_blocksize_bits);
5273
5274 if (minlen > EXT4_CLUSTERS_PER_GROUP(sb) ||
5275 start >= max_blks ||
5276 range->len < sb->s_blocksize)
5277 return -EINVAL;
5278 if (end >= max_blks)
5279 end = max_blks - 1;
5280 if (end <= first_data_blk)
5281 goto out;
5282 if (start < first_data_blk)
5283 start = first_data_blk;
5284
5285 /* Determine first and last group to examine based on start and end */
5286 ext4_get_group_no_and_offset(sb, (ext4_fsblk_t) start,
5287 &first_group, &first_cluster);
5288 ext4_get_group_no_and_offset(sb, (ext4_fsblk_t) end,
5289 &last_group, &last_cluster);
5290
5291 /* end now represents the last cluster to discard in this group */
5292 end = EXT4_CLUSTERS_PER_GROUP(sb) - 1;
5293
5294 for (group = first_group; group <= last_group; group++) {
5295 grp = ext4_get_group_info(sb, group);
5296 /* We only do this if the grp has never been initialized */
5297 if (unlikely(EXT4_MB_GRP_NEED_INIT(grp))) {
5298 ret = ext4_mb_init_group(sb, group, GFP_NOFS);
5299 if (ret)
5300 break;
5301 }
5302
5303 /*
5304 * For all the groups except the last one, last cluster will
5305 * always be EXT4_CLUSTERS_PER_GROUP(sb)-1, so we only need to
5306 * change it for the last group, note that last_cluster is
5307 * already computed earlier by ext4_get_group_no_and_offset()
5308 */
5309 if (group == last_group)
5310 end = last_cluster;
5311
5312 if (grp->bb_free >= minlen) {
5313 cnt = ext4_trim_all_free(sb, group, first_cluster,
5314 end, minlen);
5315 if (cnt < 0) {
5316 ret = cnt;
5317 break;
5318 }
5319 trimmed += cnt;
5320 }
5321
5322 /*
5323 * For every group except the first one, we are sure
5324 * that the first cluster to discard will be cluster #0.
5325 */
5326 first_cluster = 0;
5327 }
5328
5329 if (!ret)
5330 atomic_set(&EXT4_SB(sb)->s_last_trim_minblks, minlen);
5331
5332out:
5333 range->len = EXT4_C2B(EXT4_SB(sb), trimmed) << sb->s_blocksize_bits;
5334 return ret;
5335}
5336
5337/* Iterate all the free extents in the group. */
5338int
5339ext4_mballoc_query_range(
5340 struct super_block *sb,
5341 ext4_group_t group,
5342 ext4_grpblk_t start,
5343 ext4_grpblk_t end,
5344 ext4_mballoc_query_range_fn formatter,
5345 void *priv)
5346{
5347 void *bitmap;
5348 ext4_grpblk_t next;
5349 struct ext4_buddy e4b;
5350 int error;
5351
5352 error = ext4_mb_load_buddy(sb, group, &e4b);
5353 if (error)
5354 return error;
5355 bitmap = e4b.bd_bitmap;
5356
5357 ext4_lock_group(sb, group);
5358
5359 start = (e4b.bd_info->bb_first_free > start) ?
5360 e4b.bd_info->bb_first_free : start;
5361 if (end >= EXT4_CLUSTERS_PER_GROUP(sb))
5362 end = EXT4_CLUSTERS_PER_GROUP(sb) - 1;
5363
5364 while (start <= end) {
5365 start = mb_find_next_zero_bit(bitmap, end + 1, start);
5366 if (start > end)
5367 break;
5368 next = mb_find_next_bit(bitmap, end + 1, start);
5369
5370 ext4_unlock_group(sb, group);
5371 error = formatter(sb, group, start, next - start, priv);
5372 if (error)
5373 goto out_unload;
5374 ext4_lock_group(sb, group);
5375
5376 start = next + 1;
5377 }
5378
5379 ext4_unlock_group(sb, group);
5380out_unload:
5381 ext4_mb_unload_buddy(&e4b);
5382
5383 return error;
5384}
